[`ieeh-powerfactory-tools`](https://github.com/ieeh-tu-dresden/powerfactory-tools) is worth studying or using behind an adapter. It already provides typed convenience functions for:

- connecting to PowerFactory;
- activating a project;
- navigating study cases, scenarios, and variants;
- creating and altering elements;
- collecting calculation-relevant objects;
- executing load flow, short-circuit, RMS, and EMT commands;
- exporting results;
- unit normalization.

It demonstrates that your “reusable Python engineering layer” idea is sound.

But it is **not** the product. It is closer to an infrastructure adapter:

```text
Your agent workflow layer
→ your domain operations
→ optional powerfactory-tools adapter
→ official PowerFactory Python API
```

Your differentiating layer is still:

```python
