## Unit safety needs to be a first-class feature

This is more important than it first appears.

`powerfactory-tools` temporarily applies standardized units because PowerFactory projects can use different unit settings. Its standardization includes:

```text
Power: MW
Voltage: kV
Current: kA
Length: km
```

That validates the concern that this is dangerous:

```json
{ "increase": 10 }
```

Is that:

- `10 MW`?
- `10%`?
- `10 kW`?
- `10 per-unit`?
- `10 MVAr`?

Your MCP schemas should make this impossible:

```json
{
  "area": "North",
  "active_power": {
    "mode": "percentage",
    "value": 10
  },
  "reactive_power": {
    "mode": "preserve_power_factor"
  },
  "dry_run": true
}
```

And every result should include units:

```json
{
  "total_active_power_before": { "value": 923.4, "unit": "MW" },
  "total_active_power_after": { "value": 1015.7, "unit": "MW" }
}
```

